column2: Alice doesn't know why, but her legs hurt
It's hard to stand, but she manages
A voice is echoing in her head
It is for you I do this Alice, for you..
It makes Alice feel sad that the voice sounds troubled
She doesn't know why she said that
In fact, she can't remember that she just said it
She just stands there, in the cold rain
She decides to open her backpack
Nothing but what seems to be a small pocket watch. It's made of brass and has some sort of script written on it
She knew that the characters written on the watch was in a language she didn't know anyway, but in fact, she can't read or write at all
She's always dreamt of being able to read
She's even dreamt of being able to write her own book one day, but its just simply impossible for her
It has and will always continue to be just a dream of her's
There is text written on the sign
It doesn't seem to talk very much
Ah well, not that I really care
Ah well, that doesn't matter now either
You help me, and I give you..
Alright, so, you see, I have lost my key
And I was hoping that you would be able to find it for me
I mean, help me* find it
Anyway, the "something" that I want to give you is in my house over there. So, in order for you to even get that something we need to find the key
You know, sometimes it is easier to see the whole picture if you just take a step back and just look closely
So, I thought that I'll be doing that while you go looking for the key
Have you found the key yet..?
Come back when you've found it
I'll look even harder from now on
You know, my mother always used to tell me that if ou really believe in what you want to do, then there's nothing that stops you
So just keep on looking and I'm sure that you'll find the key
I'm also doing my best here you know..
How did it end up there?
Ah well, let's get inside now.
I forgot that this is not my house.
I forgot that I don't live in a house.
I sleep on the trunk over there..
..or whas is that I eat this rock..?
I don't really know, but I'm pretty sure that this is my home
I am Jimmy G. W. Harry L. Oliver R. K. Fancy by the way
Youkai is my name, I think
OMG! LOOK! Now my name is written up there! How convinient! Now I'll never forget it again!
And did you see? When I said my name, it turned all bold and fancy. Look! Youkai! Youkai...
Anyway, it's Japanese, I think. It means something, but I've forgot. You can probably google it.
Oh right, there is no google yet. I forgot
My head hurts a bit today
You know, there is a town nearby
And there is a library there
A really cute librarian, Linda, runs the place
She is very smart and probably knows what Youkai means
She is very cute, and her name is Linda
I think I'm going to go to sleep now
I hope that we meet again.
Rock, a common strategy. Building on the intuision that scissors is the most common choice
However, that intuision is faulty since it only works when you're the one who is hosting the game
Your opponent feels demotivated that way since you were the one to choose what game to play and hence picks the easiest of the bunch, scissors
I anticipated your cleverness and chose paper. Well played, but yet another win for me
Let's play again sometime! This was fun!
Paper huh. Well played, but not well enough
You see, I never underestimate my opponents
..and by not underestimating you, I knew that you wouldn't pick the most common choice, scissors.
I foreshadowed that you would pick paper since it's the seemingly weakest of the bunch and is hence the most surprising choice, however all for nought.
Well played, but yet another win for me.
Let's play again sometime! This was fun!
Scissors.. Clever.. But not clever enough!
I realised that you knew that scissors is the most common choice and hence deduced a strategy of surprise by choosing scissors anyway
I never underestimate my opponents and realised that this was your plan and hence chose rock
Well played, but yet another win for me.
Let's play again sometime! This was fun!
We played a game of rps earlier, do you remember?
...rps is short for rock paper scissors... I hope she understands that...
Anyway, I felt bad for you since you lost earlier.
So, I want us to play again!
I changed the rules a bit though, so hear me out!
To make it easier for you, I will only pick paper
However, if I do pick anything else than paper, and I so happen to win over whatever you picked, then it's a draw
In other terms, I can only win if you choose rock and I choose paper
By choosing rock you took the chance at letting me win, but by anticipating that I would anticipate you choosing something else you took the chance anyway.
However, I anticipated that you would anticipate me to anticipate your choice, and hence chose the appropriate paper!
I did it again didn't I..
He chose paper and forced a draw
Paper, a clever choice. Even though by choosing paper the chance of it becoming a draw was higher than the chance of you winning, you still took it
Too bad for you that I never underestimate my opponents and anticipated your cleverness
I knew that I couldn't win this game  against a  now experienced rpser, but I did my best to not let my pride be stamped on!
I did it again didn't I..
He chose rock and forced a draw
Scissors, as expected. The most common choice in a game of rps.
Since you're now an experienced rpser I knew that you must've anticipated that I would think that you wouldn't choose the most common choice
..but by knowing that I would think that you would be better than choosing scissors you came to the conclusion that scissors would be the most surprising choice. Well played..
But sadly I anticipated that your anticipation would lead to that conclusion and deduced that in order for me not to loose I had no choice but to choose rock
I did it again didn't I..
I'm sorry.. I can't help myself..
I don't know who you are, but here is a list of items!
Please chose one, or the game can't preceed.
Huh? My... My head hurts a bit...
It is for you I do this Alice... For you...
I really thought I heard something...
I don't... I dind't say anything... I think...
It is for your own best...
You're right... I probably just imagined it.
Um, anyway... Yo, my name is Tohi Inarashi!
But you can call me Tohi! Nice to meet you!
Hi! I'm Alice! Nice to meet you too...
Sorry for that... I'm just having this terrible headache... It makes me feel a bit ill...
Well, that's just normal... We've been travelling for a couple of hours now as well...
I think anyone can go crazy after this much bus....
Especially when you know that you're headed towards *that place*
Oh yeah, speaking of that... Why are you taking the bus to Devville?
Devville isn't really the place people usually go to for their 'great summer-adventures'...
However I suppose in this weather it wouldn't really matter wherever you went would it...
I go there every summer though, but only because I have to...
Anyway, I don't think I've seen you here before.
Usually, I spend my summers together with my family...
But this time it turned out a bit differently...
They're too busy working to take care of me, so they had to send me to some relative...
Some old uncle I've never met... He seems really boring...
I know most of the people in the town... Maybe I can tell you something about him...
I don't know...Or well, I don't remember...
Why would I care about some stupid old man's name when my own family just sends me away...?
Well, there aren't that many people living in Devville, though most of them tend to be old fishermen drinking beer...
There is a library too, with a really nice librarian though...
And there's a cool laboratory in the forest if you dare to walk there...
Well, technically, you're not allowed to go there... But..
I've never been on the inside though...
Hey, I have an idea. Won't you come with me?
It would be so much fun to do it together!
There aren't many kids in Devville, and the only one's who're there are really weird...
So I never have anyone to play with...
But it's not like it's dangerous or something...
I've been there many times, and it even appears like the place Is abandoned...
But what do you say...? It would be really fun!
Hello, plese choose now dear machine...
You need to move the ball
I'm sorry, I don't know what you're saying
What should I do with the ball?
